cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a classifier based on the Mapper algorithm, which is a method used in topological data analysis. The paper also mentions the use of PCA and autoencoders to obtain a latent space. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as possible options.
